1. open the `crappy_script.R`
2. Change the name of the function to something more meaningful
3. Add some comments to the function to describe what it does
4. Run the function to check that it works
5. Save the file
6. Open the source control extension and commit your changes
7. Add a readme file to the repository that describes what the function does and how to use it
  - create a new file called `README.md` in the folder alongside `crappy_script.R`
8. Commit your changes

Congartulations! You have successfully improved and documented a script in your repository and all changes have been changeed!